18:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Motion and Wrike AI share a solid foundation of core features including Task Management, Ai Assistant, Calendar, Collaboration. On the other hand, Wrike AI uniquely offers Templates, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Motion holds an overall score of 8/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Wrike AI scores 7/10 overall and 5/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
19:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Wrike AI comes in at a lower starting price of Free, while Motion begins at $34/mo. Wrike AI stands out by offering a free plan, giving you a risk-free way to explore the platform. Motion requires a paid subscription from the start."}]]}]
